The paper deals with the problem of whether Yao-Yao graphs are spanners, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The techniques used in the paper involve graph theory and combinatorics, which are also relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.DM (discrete mathematics). The paper also involves some numerical analysis (cs.NA) in the form of computational experiments. Finally, the problem of spanners is related to the study of graph theory and algorithms (cs.GT).
